A math student is studying Robust Statistics and is asked to find the median of the following data set: 

{3, 6, 7, 9, 10, 12, 15, 18, 20, 25, 30, 35, 45, 50, 55, 70, 90, 100, 250, 500}

Using the traditional method, the median turns out to be 25. However, if an outlier of 500 is removed, what is the new median?
